graph TD
    A[Start: User Clicks "GET SMART SUGGESTIONS"] --> B{Gather Inputs: Query, Price Range, Mood, Diet};
    
    B --> C{Primary Validation: Is **Specific Dish Name** Present?};
    
    C -- **No (No Specific Dish)** --> G{Validate Price Inputs (**Min/Max**)};
    C -- **Yes (Specific Dish)** --> F[**Override Price Filter**: Set Price Range = `0` to `9999`];
    
    G -- **Invalid Price** --> D[Display "Invalid Input" Error];
    G -- **Valid Price** --> H[Price Range = User Input **OR Inferred Mood Default**];
    
    F --> I;
    H --> I[Filter All Items by: **Price Range**, **Query**, **Diet Type**];
    
    I --> J[Sort Results by Price (**Cheapest First**)];
    
    J --> K{Identify Top Pick Candidates (**Substantial Meals Only**)};
    
    K --> L{Is **Mood** Selected?};
    
    L -- **Yes (Spicy/Heavy/Comfort)** --> M{Find Cheapest Candidate Matching **Mood Keywords**};
    L -- **No (or No Mood Match)** --> N[Select Absolute Cheapest Candidate];
    
    M --> O;
    N --> O[Final **Top Pick(s)** Determined];
    
    O --> P{Output: Render **Top Pick Card(s) Prominently**};
    O --> Q[Output: Render Remaining Items (**Sorted, Un-highlighted**)];
    O --> R[Output: Display **External Online Suggestions/Links**];
    
    P & Q & R --> S[End];

subgraph 🎯 Smart Logic Focus
    C; F; G; H; K; L; M; N
end
